Job Description:
We're seeking a dynamic Product Innovation Engineer to lead the transformation of luxury soft toy manufacturing across Southeast Asia. Based in Vietnam, you’ll drive new product development, elevate quality standards, and modernize supplier networks using cutting-edge technology, sustainable materials, and cross-industry collaboration.
Key Focus: Product innovation driving both radical breakthrough and incremental improvements
Geographic Scope: Vietnam-based with regional SE Asia responsibility
Innovation Mission: Transform product excellence through evolving technology and design thinking

Job Descriptions:
1. Product Development & Innovation
- Lead new product design using design thinking and customer-focused methodologies;
- Introduce sustainable materials in line with supply chain capabilities;
- Collaborate with material science experts to enhance product performance and sustainability;
- Support innovation protection through IP strategies and patent applications;
- Oversee new product introductions (NPI) across regional sites, ensuring luxury brand quality standards are met.

2. Quality Excellence
- Contribute to developing customer-focused quality assessment frameworks;
- Digitize quality records and leverage machine learning for defect detection;
- Conduct root cause analysis and product testing in alignment with global quality standards.

3. Supplier Development
- Collaborate with Tier 2–3 suppliers to modernize materials and processes;
- Co-invest in innovation and quality upgrades;
- Leverage cross-sector technologies with universities and consultants.

4. Process & Technology Implementation
- Utilize production data to optimize operational efficiency and product quality;
- Integrate automation, robotics, and AI for scalable and flexible manufacturing;
- Develop standard operating procedures (SOPs) that reflect evolving technologies and market expectations.

5. Regional Coordination
- Drive innovation cycles (6–18 months) across Southeast Asia;
- Coordinate technology transfer and product launches in Vietnam, China, and Indonesia;
- Facilitate knowledge sharing, establish research partnerships, and build capabilities across regional teams.

Job Introduction
We are hiring a strategic and hands-on Senior Industrial Innovation Engineer to lead manufacturing innovation across Southeast Asia. Based in Vietnam, this role focuses on process optimization, supplier development, and digital transformation through Industry 4.0 technologies. You'll drive end-to-end innovation cycles and regional coordination to support company premium product standards.
Location: Vietnam (with frequent travel to Dongguan / Guangzhou / Shenzhen / Shanghai, China, Indonesia & SE Asia)
Reports to: Supplier Relationship Manager


Job Descriptions:
1. Strategic Innovation & Process Improvement
- Lead 6–18 month innovation cycles, from concept to full production implementation;
- Drive Industry 4.0 integration, including IoT, robotics, and digital manufacturing systems;
- Scout, assess, and implement emerging technologies with global R&D collaboration;
- Oversee prototyping, process testing, and roadmap execution for scalable innovations;
- Lead continuous improvement initiatives using lean, Six Sigma, and automation.

2. Supplier Development & Performance
- Manage Tier 2 supplier relationships across China, Vietnam, Indonesia, and SE Asia;
- Conduct audits, technical reviews, and capability assessments for new product components;
- Implement quality assurance systems, performance KPIs, and risk mitigation plans;
- Drive joint innovation programs and technology transfer with supplier partners;
- Enhance supplier capacity and ensure alignment with company's premium standards.

3. Manufacturing Excellence & Operational Optimization
- Analyze manufacturing processes across regional sites and identify efficiency gaps;
- Lead layout design, automation deployment, and time-motion studies;
- Develop and standardize SOPs, work instructions, and best practices;
- Monitor and improve KPIs: productivity, yield, cycle time, and quality;
- Lead root cause analysis and corrective action for technical production issues.

4. Regional Coordination & Technical Leadership
- Travel 40–50% to coordinate cross-border projects and innovation rollouts;
- Support new facility setups, line optimization, and equipment installation;
- Facilitate technology transfer and best-practice sharing across countries;
- Guide technical teams during scaling, troubleshooting, and training;
- Collaborate with stakeholders across functions, regions, and cultures.

- Giám sát quá trình thi công, quản lý tổ đội, nhà thầu tại các dự án đang thi công, sửa chữa, bảo trì;
- Đề xuất mua hàng vật tư, theo tiến độ thực hiện thi công và báo cáo trực tiếp cho Trưởng phòng;
- Tiếp nhận thông tin và xử lý các công tác sửa chữa, bảo trì căn hộ/chung cư theo yêu cầu chủ đầu tư, cư dân, ban quản lý;
- Quản lý công nhân xây dựng: điều phối nhân sự, hướng dẫn xử lý, sửa chữa các vấn đề phát sinh của căn hộ, tòa nhà chung cư;
- Lập báo cáo định kỳ báo các tiến độ công việc;
- Di chuyển và làm việc tại các dự án theo yêu cầu của cấp trên;
- Các công việc theo yêu cầu của cấp trên.

Job Requirements:
- Nam từ 25 – 35 tuổi;
- Tốt nghiệp Cao đẳng trở lên chuyên ngành Xây Dựng và các ngành liên quan;
- Có từ 2 - 4 năm kinh nghiệm trong lĩnh vực xây dựng dân dụng;
- Có kinh nghiệm giải quyết sự cố trong xây dựng, hệ thống điện, nước, xử lý nước thải;
- Có kỹ năng giao tiếp với cư dân, biết đọc bản vẽ kỹ thuật là một lợi thế.

